						<summary>

						<p>Stone fixed in the old <hi rend="italic">Kuḍiraivāhana maṇḍapa</hi> in the village.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 18th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It states that the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> was constructed by Nāraṇappa Nāyudu, son of Appayya-Nāyuḍu who was the son of Kaḍiyam Sūrappa-Nāyaḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
